This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper discusses a semi-supervised bootstrapping approach for NER which involves using a small set of training data to identify named entities and then using this information to generate patterns for identifying named entities in the test set. This approach involves machine learning and pattern recognition techniques, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
